<p>Font weight is directly inherited from the U.S. Web Design Standards.</p>

<p><strong>Quick usage reference:</strong></p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>SCSS variable</th>
      <th>CSS class</th>
      <th>Font weight</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>$font-bold</strong></td>
      <td><strong><code class="highlighter-rouge">p-bold</code></strong></td>
      <td><strong>700</strong></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>$font-normal</td>
      <td><code class="highlighter-rouge">p-normal</code> (only needs to be used to be used to override another class)</td>
      <td>400</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
